==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pecan
<hw>Pe*can"</hw> <pr>(p⟦esl⟧*k⟦acr⟧n")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pacane</ets> the nut.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species of
hickory (<spn>Carya oliv⟦ae⟧formis</spn>), growing in North America,
chiefly in the Mississippi valley and in Texas, where it is one of the
largest of forest trees; also, its fruit, a smooth, oblong nut, an inch
or an inch and a half long, with a thin shell and well-flavored
meat.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>pacane</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

